CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 21, 1959, pg. A18 reads: "Federation Officers - Seated clockwise around a table are officers of the Pennsylvania Sate Federation of Negro Women's Clubs. They are discussing plans for the annual state convention which will convene in Pittsburgh next July.  They are Mmes. Hallie Capp of Kane; Ethel Walls, Mary Poen, Iona Richardson and Sarah Brown, all of Pittsburgh; Mrs. Eva B. Nelson, president, of McKeesport; Charlotte Morris of Aliquippa, and Ellis Blockson of Sewickley. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eight women, officers of the Pennsylvania State Federation of Negro Women's Clubs, clockwise: Hallie Capp, Ethel Walls, Mary Poen, Iona Richardson, Sarah Brown, Eva B. Nelson, Charlotte Morris, and Ellis Blockson, seated for meeting in church interior, another version
